+# Additional Smoke-Test Review: `testpage-260319-194642`
+
+## Scope
+
+Reviewed `pages/TestPage/base/testpage.jsx` with `README.md` and `BUGS.md` as local context. This pass focused on obvious runtime bugs, i18n problems, mobile-first UX, and React anti-patterns.
+
+## Findings
+
+1. [P0] Broken i18n hook import path — `@/components/useI18n` is inconsistent with the repo-wide `@/components/i18n` import and no matching `useI18n` module exists in this checkout. FIX: import `useI18n` from `@/components/i18n`.
+2. [P1] Raw exception messages leak untranslated browser text — `err.message` is rendered directly, so users can see browser/network strings like `Failed to fetch`. FIX: map catch paths to translated UI messages instead of exposing raw exception text.
+3. [P1] `test_page.*` translation keys are missing from the repo catalog — the code references `test_page.fetch_failed`, `test_page.delete_failed`, `test_page.title`, and `test_page.no_items`, but those keys are not present in the repo translation sources in this snapshot. FIX: add the missing keys to the translation catalog and provide explicit fallbacks if needed.
+4. [P1] Single `deletingId` state breaks overlapping deletes — one in-flight delete can clear the loading state for another item, re-enabling buttons too early. FIX: track deleting state per item id or disable all delete actions while any delete is pending.
+5. [P2] `useEffect` references a later `const` function — the effect calls `fetchItems()` before its `const` declaration, violating the repo TDZ-safety rule. FIX: move `fetchItems` above the effect or inline the loader inside the effect.
+6. [P2] List row layout is not mobile-safe for long item names — long names can squeeze or overlap the delete action on narrow screens. FIX: give the text its own flex child with `flex-1 min-w-0` and wrapping or truncation.
+7. [P2] Error state has no recovery action — after a transient fetch failure the page offers no retry path besides full-page reload. FIX: add a retry button wired to `fetchItems()`.
+
+## Summary
+
+Total: 7 findings (1 P0, 3 P1, 3 P2, 0 P3)
